Class IntSetN1RXPFirstImprovingGraphAllMovesMakerMT

  • java.lang.Object
    • graph.packing.IntSetN1RXPFirstImprovingGraphAllMovesMakerMT
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, AllChromosomeMakerClonableIntf, AllChromosomeMakerIntf

    public class IntSetN1RXPFirstImprovingGraphAllMovesMakerMT
extends java.lang.Object
implements AllChromosomeMakerClonableIntf
    Multi-threaded version of the IntSetN1RXPFirstImprovingGraphAllMovesMaker class. Class is specific to the 1-packing (MWIS) and 2-packing graph problems.

    Title: popt4jlib

    Description: A Parallel Meta-Heuristic Optimization Library in Java

      • createAllChromosomes

        public java.util.Vector createAllChromosomes(java.lang.Object chromosome,
                                             java.util.HashMap params)
                                      throws OptimizerException
        implements the N_{-1+P} neighborhood for sets of integers.
        Specified by:
        createAllChromosomes in interface AllChromosomeMakerIntf
        Parameters:
        chromosome - Object Set<Integer node-id>
        params - HashMap must contain the following key-value pairs:
        • <"dls.intsetneighborhoodfilter", IntSetNeighborhoodFilterIntf filter>
        • <"dls.graph", Graph g> the original problem graph
        It may also optionally contain the following pairs:
        • <"dls.intsetneighborhoodmaxnodestotry", Integer max_nodes> which if present will indicate the maximum number of nodes to try to remove from the current solution in the "1RXP" local search.
        • <"dls.numthreads", Integer num_threads> which if present denotes the number of threads that an a-synchronous batch-task executor will create and use to execute the generated tasks, default is 1.
        • <"dls.fpabte", FasterParallelAsynchronousBatchTaskExecutor extor> which if present is the parallel executor to use, default is null. If such an executor is present, the "dls.numthreads" value is ignored.
        • <"dls.lock_graph", Boolean val> which if present and false, indicates that the graph and its elements will be accessed without any synchronization. Default is true.

        The filter must specify what ints to be tried for addition to the set given an int to be removed from the set.

        Returns:
        Vector Vector<Set<Integer nodeid> >
        Throws:
        OptimizerException - if any of the parameters are incorrectly set

      • createSet

        protected java.util.Set createSet(java.util.Set res,
                                  int rmid,
                                  java.util.List tryids,
                                  int maxcard,
                                  java.util.HashMap params)
        hook method in the context of the Template Method Design Pattern. Sub-classes with more domain knowledge may override this method to modify the behavior of this move-maker. This method implements a depth-first search on the space of neighbors to find the first improving solution which it returns immediately (the soln is a maximally-improving soln in the DF fashion). The implementation is recursive.
        Parameters:
        res - Set // IntSet
        rmid - Integer
        tryids - List // List<Integer>
        maxcard - int
        params - HashMap must contain the pair <"dls.graph", Graph g>, and may optionally contain the pair <"dls.lock_graph", Boolean val> which if present and val is false, indicates no read-locking of the graph elements
        Returns:
        Set // IntSet
